cs.CE, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL

This paper deals with the representation and management of metadata in computational molecular engineering workflows. The use of ontologies and semantic interoperability suggests a focus on knowledge representation and reasoning, which is a common theme in the subfield of computer engineering (cs.CE). The paper also discusses data provenance, which is a key aspect of database management (cs.DB). The use of ontologies and semantic interoperability also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper introduces two ontologies, which suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
